    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Add your <strong>Cumberland sausages</strong> to a baking tray (use <strong>tin foil</strong> to avoid mess!)</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until the sausages are golden and cooked through</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/italian-style-sausage-basil-and-courgette-salad/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>basil </strong>finely, including the stalks</p><p>Chop your <strong>heritage tomatoes</strong> in half</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/italian-style-sausage-basil-and-courgette-salad/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>Dijon mustard</strong>, <strong>chopped basil</strong>,<strong> balsamic vinegar</strong>, and 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>sugar</strong> in a very large bowl and give it a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>Italian dressing</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/italian-style-sausage-basil-and-courgette-salad/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel lengths off your <strong>courgette[s]</strong> until you end up with a pile of courgette 'ribbons'</p><p>Shave your<strong> Italian hard cheese</strong> with a peeler, until you end up with a pile of cheese shavings</p><p>Once you can't peel anymore, crumble the remaining cheese</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/italian-style-sausage-basil-and-courgette-salad/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Tear your <strong>ciabatta[s]</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the <strong>ciabatta pieces</strong> to a separate baking tray (or two!) with your <strong>dried oregano</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 5-6 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/italian-style-sausage-basil-and-courgette-salad/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once done, remove the <strong>sausages</strong> from the oven and slice them on a diagonal into bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/italian-style-sausage-basil-and-courgette-salad/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then add <strong>all of the ingredients</strong> to the <strong>Italian dressing</strong> and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your<strong> Italian-style sausage, basil & courgette salad</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/italian-style-sausage-basil-and-courgette-salad/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Italian-style sausage, basil & courgette salad</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
